T1  - Theory and Application of an Optimizing Procedure for Lock Box Location Analysis
AU  - Nauss, Robert M.
AU  - Markland, Robert E.
Y1  - 1981/08/01
PY  - 1981
DA  - 1981/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.27.8.855
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.27.8.855
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 855
EP  - 865
VL  - 27
IS  - 8
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper describes the theory, development, and application of an optimizing procedure for solving lock box location problems. Such problems have become increasingly important to banks, corporations, and governmental agencies in their quest for more efficient cash management. Extensive discussion of practical data collection and modeling aspects is provided. An optimizing procedure for solving the problem is discussed, and computational results are reported.
AB  - This paper describes the theory, development, and application of an optimizing procedure for solving lock box location problems. Such problems have become increasingly important to banks, corporations, and governmental agencies in their quest for more efficient cash management. Extensive discussion of practical data collection and modeling aspects is provided. An optimizing procedure for solving the problem is discussed, and computational results are reported.
